headlines.description: — Ja Morant had 35 points and 10 assists, De'Anthony Melton and Dillon Brooks each added 20 points, and the Memphis Grizzlies beat the Washington Wizards 125-111 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant, Grizzlies pull away early, beat Wizards 125-111

headlines.description: — Kemba Walker had 25 points and six assists, and the Boston Celtics took advantage of a late scratch of All-Star Kawhi Leonard and held off the Los Angeles Clippers 117-112 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Walker's 25 lift Celtics over Kawhi-less Clippers 117-112

headlines.description: — Trae Young took over late and made sure Nate McMillan would win his debut as interim coach of the Atlanta Hawks.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hawks win McMillan's debut, top Heat 94-80

events.name: New York Knicks at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Trey Lyles scored a season-high 18 points, Dejounte Murray added 17 and the San Antonio Spurs used a balanced effort to beat New York 119-83 on Tuesday night, ending the Knicks’ three-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lyles, Murray lead Spurs to victory, snapping Knicks' streak

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 37 points, 11 assists and 10 rebounds for his ninth triple-double of the season and 50th of his career, and the Denver Nuggets trounced Milwaukee 128-97 on Tuesday to snap the Bucks’ five-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic's triple-double leads Nuggets to 128-97 rout of Bucks

events.name: Phoenix Suns at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Dario Šarić scored 10 of his 21 points in the fourth quarter, Mikal Bridges added 19 and the Phoenix Suns overcame Devin Booker's ejection for a 114-104 victory over the Los Angeles Lakers on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns overcome Booker's ejection, hold off Lakers 114-104
